name: duck

attributes.attribute: goddess of the source of France’s river Seine
depicted sailing in a boat whose prow was shaped into a duck’s head
symbol of Celtic divinity, especially of goddesses

sources: Monaghan, Patricia. The Encyclopedia of Celtic Mythology and Folklore. Checkmark Books, 2008.
text: Symbolic of divinity in Celtic culture, the duck is an animal associated with Sequana, the goddess of the source of France's Seine river. Depicted voyaging on a boat with a duck-headed prow, the goddess exemplifies the significance of birds, particularly female deities, in Celtic symbolism.
